"Senior Policy Analyst - RES006061
You will work with a variety of health, education and government stakeholders to gather data, forecast and assess health human resource needs, identify solutions and strategies for ensuring critical health human resources are available. In addition, you will answer information requests from members of the public and government on a variety of topics related to health human resources.
To join this challenging, innovative and supportive working environment, the successful candidates will have a solid knowledge of health policy issues, public policy development, forecasting and data analysis techniques, statistical software packaages, and an understanding of government structures and decision-making processes.
Typically, the knowledge and skills required for this position would have been gained through completion of a degree in social science, health administration, statistics, economics, applied mathematics or a related discipline, along with experience in public policy development.
 A competitive salary;
Comprehensive benefits package including pension;
Vacation, scheduled days off (SDO) and other types of leave;
Advancement opportunities; and
Flexible work arrangements.
